<sn><md>#### Stone Age (Paleolithic Age)

`Stone Age`, `Stone`, `Tools`

In world history, the Stone Age refers to a stage in the evolution of humans and their society `when the main materials used for making tools were stones`. <br>
The Stone Age began around `5 million years ago`. <br>
It lasted until around `3500 BCE`,<br>
 which is about `5500 years ago`.

According to historians, this period is divided into three stages: Old Stone Age, Middle Stone Age, and New Stone Age.

| Stage            | Description                    |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------ |
|`Old` Stone Age    | Age of fire discovery          |
| `Middle` Stone Age | Improved use of stone tools    |
| `New` Stone Age    | Advanced stone tool technology |

</md></sn><sn><md>#### Old Stone Age 

Early Paleolithic Age<br>
The Old Stone Age `lasted` for a very `long period` of time. It continued until the beginning of the Middle Stone Age. The most important discovery of people in the Old Stone Age was `fire`🔥

```text id="9g8v2q"
Old Stone Age
        │
        ├── Long duration
        │
        └── Discovery of fire
```
